<h1>念</h1><p class=neha><span style="color:#000099;">niàn</span><span class=alesi>(nian4)</span> <span class=lesi>// pronunciation of 念 in Mandarin Pinyin</span></p><h2>Basic information about 念</h2><div class=abo>
<p><b>Unihan definition:</b> <a href="/dictionary/think" style="color:black;">think</a> <a href="/dictionary/of" style="color:black;">of</a>, <a href="/dictionary/recall" style="color:black;">recall</a>, study</p><p><b>Number of strokes:</b> 8<br><small>Examples of other characters consisting of 8 strokes: <a href="/character/的" title="de: possessive, adjectival suffix">的</a>, <a href="/character/和" title="he2: harmony, peace; peaceful, calm">和</a>, <a href="/character/国" title="guo2: nation, country, nation-state">国</a>, <a href="/character/到" title="dao4: go to, arrive, been to">到</a>, <a href="/character/所" title="suo3: place, location; numerary adjunct">所</a>, <a href="/character/事" title="shi4: affair, matter, business; to serve; accident, incident">事</a>, <a href="/character/经" title="jing1: classic works; pass through">经</a>, <a href="/character/法" title="fa3: law, rule, regulation, statute; France, French">法</a>, <a href="/character/学" title="xue2: learning, knowledge; school">学</a>, <a href="/character/现" title="xian4: appear, manifest, become visible">现</a></small></p><p><b>Radical:</b> <a href="/character/心" title="Kangxi radical 61">心</a>&nbsp;61.4</p><p><b>HSK level:</b> 5 <br><small>Other HSK 5 characters: <a href="/character/显" title="xian3: manifest, display; evident, clear">显</a>, <a href="/character/装" title="zhuang1: dress, clothes, attire; fill">装</a>, <a href="/character/农" title="nong2: agriculture, farming; farmer">农</a>, <a href="/character/曾" title="ceng2: already; sign of past">曾</a>, <a href="/character/委" title="wei3: appoint, send, commission">委</a>, <a href="/character/青" title="qing1: blue, green, black; young">青</a>, <a href="/character/武" title="wu3: military; martial, warlike">武</a>, <a href="/character/企" title="qi3: plan a project; stand on tiptoe">企</a>, <a href="/character/称" title="cheng1: call; name, brand; address; say">称</a>, <a href="/character/势" title="shi4: power, force; tendency">势</a> <a href="/character-list/hsk/level-5" title="List of HSK 5 characters" style="white-space: nowrap;">more hsk 5 charaters &raquo;</a></small></p><p><b>Frequency rank:</b> 477</p><p><b><a href="/character-list/general-standard" title="Table of General Standard Chinese Characters">General standard</a> index number:</b> 1177</p><p><b>Examples of words containing this character:</b> <a href="/dictionary/信念" title="xin4 nian4">信念</a>, <a href="/dictionary/可念" title="ke3 nian4">可念</a>, <a href="/dictionary/唱念" title="chang4 nian4">唱念</a>, <a href="/dictionary/妄念" title="wang4 nian4">妄念</a>, <a href="/dictionary/念佛" title="nian4 fo2">念佛</a>, <a href="/dictionary/念力" title="nian4 li4">念力</a>, <a href="/dictionary/念叨" title="nian4 dao5">念叨</a>, <a href="/dictionary/念咒" title="nian4 zhou4">念咒</a>, <a href="/dictionary/念日" title="nian4 ri4">念日</a>, <a href="/dictionary/念书" title="nian4 shu1">念书</a>, <a href="/dictionary/念珠" title="nian4 zhu1">念珠</a>, <a href="/dictionary/念经" title="nian4 jing1">念经</a>, <a href="/dictionary/念旧" title="nian4 jiu4">念旧</a>, <a href="/dictionary/念诵" title="nian4 song4">念诵</a>, <a href="/dictionary/念头" title="nian4 tou5">念头</a>, <a href="/dictionary/思念" title="si1 nian4">思念</a>, <a href="/dictionary/悼念" title="dao4 nian4">悼念</a>, <a href="/dictionary/惦念" title="dian4 nian4">惦念</a>, <a href="/dictionary/想念" title="xiang3 nian4">想念</a>, <a href="/dictionary/意念" title="yi4 nian4">意念</a>, <a href="/dictionary/感念" title="gan3 nian4">感念</a>, <a href="/dictionary/怀念" title="huai2 nian4">怀念</a>, <a href="/dictionary/悬念" title="xuan2 nian4">悬念</a>, <a href="/dictionary/恋念" title="lian4 nian4">恋念</a>, <a href="/dictionary/挂念" title="gua4 nian4">挂念</a></p></div><h2>English translation (based on CEDICT):</h2><div class=ceent><div style="background:#dddddd;float:both;font-family: monospace;">唸|念[<span style="color:#000099;">niàn</span>]:</div> <div style="float:left;padding-left:15px;">- variant of <a href="/dictionary/念">念</a>[nian4], to read aloud<br></div><div style="clear:both;"></div></div><div class=ceent><div style="background:#dddddd;float:both;font-family: monospace;">念[<span style="color:#000099;">niàn</span>]:</div> <div style="float:left;padding-left:15px;">- to read<br>- to study (a subject)<br>- to attend (a school)<br>- to read aloud<br>- to miss (sb)<br>- idea<br>- remembrance<br>- twenty (banker's anti-fraud numeral corresponding to <a href="/dictionary/廿">廿</a>, 20)<br></div><div style="clear:both;"></div></div><h2>Details</h2><p><b>Unicode code point:</b> U+5FF5</p></div>

